#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_linear.py
Linear workload O(n).
Usage: python sample_linear.py <N>
"""
import sys
import time
import random

def linear(n):
    total = 0
    for i in range(n):
        total += (i % 7) * (i % 13)
    return total

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 10000
    start = time.time()
    out = linear(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, result={out}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_log.py
Logarithmic-ish workload (binary search style). Simulated by repeatedly halving a range (O(log n)).
Usage: python sample_log.py <N>
"""
import sys
import time

def binary_like(n):
    x = n
    steps = 0
    while x > 1:
        x = x // 2
        # small work per iteration
        steps += 1
    return steps

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 1000000
    start = time.time()
    steps = binary_like(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, steps={steps}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_n2.py
Quadratic workload O(n^2) with nested loops.
Usage: python sample_n2.py <N>
Note: choose moderate N (e.g., 100..200) for practical runs.
"""
import sys
import time

def n2(n):
    cnt = 0
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            cnt += (i + j) % 3
    return cnt

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 200
    start = time.time()
    out = n2(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, result={out}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_n3.py
Cubic workload O(n^3) demonstration (small N recommended).
Usage: python sample_n3.py <N>
Note: n=30 is already 27k iterations; keep N small during collection.
"""
import sys
import time

def n3(n):
    s = 0
    for a in range(n):
        for b in range(n):
            for c in range(n):
                s += (a * b * c) % 5
    return s

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 30
    start = time.time()
    out = n3(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, result={out}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_nlogn.py
O(n log n) workload: build list of size n and sort (timing dominated by sort).
Usage: python sample_nlogn.py <N>
"""
import sys
import time
import random

def nlogn(n):
    data = [random.random() for _ in range(n)]
    data.sort()
    return data[0], data[-1]

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 5000
    start = time.time()
    mins, maxs = nlogn(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, min={mins:.6f}, max={maxs:.6f}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")

    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 5000

#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
sample_nlogn.py
O(n log n) workload: build list of size n and sort (timing dominated by sort).
Usage: python sample_nlogn.py <N>
"""
import sys
import time
import random

def nlogn(n):
    data = [random.random() for _ in range(n)]
    data.sort()
    return data[0], data[-1]

if __name__ == "__main__":
    n = int(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 5000
    start = time.time()
    mins, maxs = nlogn(n)
    elapsed = time.time() - start
    print(f"n={n}, min={mins:.6f}, max={maxs:.6f}, time_s={elapsed:.6f}")
